values:
It's a good thing I've been singing all day then! PHEW! I'm sure to cover all my bases by the time the day is done...<br /><br />So, so far today, the power went off yesterday causing our computers to be shut off last night, Novell (the email system) was on the fritz for a while this morning, a new Muse&nbsp; cd is coming out, the lead from Radiohead is going to release a solo album later this summer, Carmen got word that all the boards we were told to bring downstairs yesterday had to be brought right back upstairs, and I went to help Andrea box up some films for shipping and we ended up spending like an hour or more in the mail room. I do declare that I've spent more time in the mail room today than I have in the last week! And I'll probably be spending more there later today....&nbsp; Boy! it's been random today! Oh wait. Just kidding, one more thing. We probably need to make another binder today, which means I'll have to do it right away b/c I can't stay late tonight b/c of my doctor's appt. Hm. <br /><br />Although I've already gotten a phone call from a credit card company (who I told in no uncertain terms how the hell did they get my number and take me off any lists they have) and from the doctor's asking if i can come in early. Hm. let me just see if I can leave work in the middle of the day. Riiight. <br /><br />*shrug* With the way everything's been going, who the hell knows what's in store for the rest of the day! <br /><br />Here is a funny quote from Brandon Crall that I keep wanting to say here at work but haven't found a good opportunity: <br /><br />
<pre class="WMmessagebody">[14:42] Brandon Crall: oh no problem. we are both at work. it's part of the <br />process<br />[14:42] curliegal1984: i find that so amusing now<br />[14:42] Brandon Crall: oh oh...being in traffic, you have to use my joke. If <br />someone ever wants to know why something is late, just tell them traffic was/is <br />heavy.<br />[14:42] curliegal1984: i can say "im at work" and it's true<br />[14:43] curliegal1984: hahaha!!!!<br />[14:43] curliegal1984: that's great!<br />[14:43] Brandon Crall: yeah. isn't that wonderful and work appropriate?</pre>
<br />And&nbsp; also, I saw my cousin Nikki's away message last night and I sat there pondering it for a few minutes. I think it's one of the best things I've heard lately. Here tis: <br /><br /><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Courier;"><font size="2">If you want to know where your heart is, look to where your mind goes when it wanders.</font><br /><br /></span>So true, non?&nbsp; Being mostly not busy allows my mind to wander a lot all the time. At work, driving to and fro, at home, at the gym. *sigh*&nbsp; <br /><br />YAY PAYCHECK!!!!!!! :-D And it appears I'm being paid more than I was originally told!!! COOL!!!!!!!!!!&nbsp;

So today was another primarily uneventful day at work. Good did come of it tho: I chatted w/ Gregor and looked at his pictures for like 2 hours! Shazaam!&nbsp; It was great! :) I havent talked to him for that long of a period lately, and I really got a chance to have a good good look at his pics. I also chatted a bit with B. Crall and J. Sumner, pretty much per usual. HAHA&nbsp;&nbsp; Actually, I did exchange a few lines with B. Bouwman and The Chad as well! I found out that Dieneke did really good in her marathon this weekend, that Traverse was awesome (of course!) and Chad actually had work to do and seemed in slightly better spirits. Capital!

Several bad things happened tho. Well, not terrible, but not great. The package that I shipped on Friday (at 2 in the afternoon) was not received this morning at whatever time Wendy came to me. I have no idea why it didnt get there seeing as I sent it PRIORITY OVERNIGHT. HELLO?! DUR! It should have freaking been there on Saturday! Gosh sometimes Fed Ex pisses me off! We tracked it and the damn thing was still scheduled to have been checked out at 7:01am this morning and was basically sitting on the truck waiting for delivery at 7:44am. I'm pretty sure it was like 11:30 when she came rushing to me, so that meant that it was 11:30 and the damn package was still on the fucking truck! ARGH! People are morons. Anyways, then apparently there is a person by the name of Heather Francis who no longer exists at Doner. Instead there is a Heather Yuhas. And Heather Yuhas is supposed to have an extension and a cube assignment (but no email for some reason) and yet, when I go to find her cube, it is inhabited by a Mr. John Somethingorother. WTF. So poor Heather hasn't received her copy of the Expedia Deck that I so lovingly b&amp;w and color copied for her. Well damn.&nbsp;

The last eventful thing of the day occured when I went to retrieve some interoffice envelopes and I ran into Keran and Carmen. I volunteered myself to help Carmen move a bunch of old Creative boards from the 3rd floor to the "Media Arts room" which apparently is in the basement. Little did I know that that also included stuffing the stupid cardboard/ styrofoam boards in with all the other millions of boards and piles of papers and boxes and leather carrying cases. Or that Carmen would drop a bunch of them on my toes. hahah She felt so bad, it was amusing. Not that having them on my foot felt great, but then I did the same exact thing again like 5 minutes later. I also backed into the door and narrowly missed smashing my fingers in the cart. haha yeah I told Carmen I think my lunar moon was not following the path of my rising tide. She looked at me like "wtf" and I said, "well you know... how people blame their clumsiness on the full moon or something"&nbsp; then she laughed for like 10 minutes and kept apologizing profusely while we lugged these things up and down the stairs :-P&nbsp;

So pretty much another boring day at the office. Oh Donald Trump, eat your heart out.&nbsp;


As for yesterday and the weekend: glorious! The heat is so freaking wonderful, it made me want to swim all day long! Too bad I never got to :(&nbsp;&nbsp; But after I took that 4 hour nap on friday when I came home to get rid of the migraine, I felt pretty good all weekend. Dad and I made the trekk to Dayton to visit the Grandparents, and Aunts and Uncles and Cousins, and everyone had a really really nice time. This is very surprising b/c usually I can't wait to come home as soon as we get there. But this time Uncle Tony and Aunt Judy were in from AZ and I think they really had some good time to catch up with their siblings. No one fought, no one made an ass out of themselves, there were no awkward silences. Everyone goofed around and stuff. Even Grandma! whoa that's crazy talk.&nbsp; Diana and Sophia and I got a chance to see eachother, which I love, and want to do again this summer as a girls weekend. Not sure how that's going to work out, but we'll see.&nbsp;

Then yesterday was Aunt Rory's bday celebration with the rest of the Dygert family. This includes Aunt Jackie and Uncle BJ, and their wonderfully funny, crazy kids, Jack (4), Nicole (6) and Danielle (13). Those 2 little ones absolutely crack me up. They pick at each other, and fight, and laugh, and whine with eachother so much it's hysterical. I can't even really begin to say. I hope Aunt Rory sends me her pictures b/c she has some CLASSIC ones of Jack. He is just WAY TOO CUTE for his own good. And I DONT think it's FAIR that my YOUNGER cousin Danielle is 2 INCHES TALLER THAN ME. *POUT* Swear to God, her shoulders are way above mine. That girl is an absolute bean pole with legs up to her ears! All I can say is her parents are gonna have a hellavatime keeping those Southern boys away from her! She is one beautiful girl! (And I'm totally not just saying that b/c I'm her older cousin...)&nbsp; But they're moving to Georgia pretty soon! :( &nbsp;It makes me so sad! I love those guys! But they are almost done building their house and I know they will absolutely love it, so I can't stay sad for that long.&nbsp;

Alright, well I'm going to go look at more pictures from overseas and try to get my laptop working enough to take the pics off of my camera from yesterday and the weekend. There's a really funny one of Diana and I goofing around with sparklers and her mom too. We look like we're high with all the smoke from the sparklers. haha what an amusing weekend! I dont want to go to the doctor's tomorrow after work! UGH! this sucks. lol and I still need to make my dentist appointment for my cavity :-\&nbsp; Maybe I can balance it out by making a hair appointment? Or maybe I can convince Mom that I really need to go work-clothes-shopping this weekend since I'm not going to Kentucky?! Hm... I'll have to try that.

hehe This was an amusing message to find when I got back to my desk this evening. It's from good ol' Jimmar, whom I havent talked to or seen in FOREVER! I miss him!&nbsp; I miss "our handshake" haha :) good times in E/F...valley 3

Jimmar: Feel better quick cuz the world needs your smile
&nbsp; Times get "intense" that's what makes life worthwhile
&nbsp; you got this, trust me, just let me tell you how
&nbsp; show that sore throats who's boss with all of your style
&nbsp; holla!&nbsp;

And yes, I did stay later tonight again *sigh* I only stayed an hour, but I guess it's just that by the time 5:30 rolls around I just want to get out of there! I should really be expecting to stay late all the time given that it's a "real person's job" (technically). Oh well.&nbsp;

And yeah, my throat really still hurts. Dinner helped a bit, and I suspect ice cream would too since it's cold, but other than that, I'm gulping down water. The Pistons are kind of pissing me off, and House was just really weird tonight! A good final show, no doubt, but it was totally weird. Oh well... I'll have to see who won American Idol tomorrow morning (yes I missed it tonight and no I dont really care)&nbsp;

:-P&nbsp;

I should go figure out what I'm wearing to work and make my lunch. Ho hum. then to bed for me. I havent been sleeping all that great again lately :-\&nbsp; but OH! I have to email my resume to this guy at Stryker... he called me at work yesterday and wondered if I was still interested in a position. I was like "uh...I'm at work... how about for fall?" haha

it's my last day at the Registrar's office till Fall!!! ack! *sniffle* what am I gonna do!? it's 4:55pm and i'm like stalling leaving :-P&nbsp;

*sigh* it's been a great year working with all the women, i'm really gonna miss them till fall. Everyone's been asking me am i coming back in the fall??? the answer is YES! and today at the taco luncheon we had, someone made the suggestion that b/c i was lebanese, I should come up with 20 recipies for the women and have them all make something and we'll have a Lebanese potluck luncheon. haha cool! so this is good b/c mom, aunt rory and i will work it out this summer :)

gosh i love this place, it cracks me up!&nbsp;

(and I dont just love working here b/c of the food... tho that's a plus, for sure!) :)&nbsp;

Joyce gave me a card and a bag of m&amp;ms b/c she was afraid that Doner wouldnt have sweets laying around the office all the time like we do here... she's so awesome!&nbsp;

alright they're turning off the lights! time to goooo!!!!!
